{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place strawberries into mixing bowl and mill <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer into a large bowl and set aside.","Place puffed brown rice into mixing bowl and blend <b>Turbo\/2 sec\/1 time<b>. Transfer into bowl with strawberries and stir to combine. Set bowl aside.","Place sunflower seeds into mixing bowl and grind <b>1 min\/70°C\/speed 6<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and grind <b>40 sec\/70°C\/speed 6<b> <strong>.<\/strong> ","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add coconut oil and grind <b>40 sec\/70°C\/speed 6<b> <strong>,<\/strong> until mixture resembles damp breadcrumbs.","Add rice malt syrup and cook <b>4 min\/80°C\/speed 3<b> <strong>,<\/strong> <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong> <strong>,<\/strong> adding vanilla through hole in mixing bowl lid during last 20 seconds of cooking time.","Transfer into bowl with strawberry mixture and fold together using spatula. Allow to cool for 1-2 minutes.","Using damp hands, roll 2 teaspoons of mixture into a ball and transfer into a sealable container. Repeat with remaining mixture (makes approx. 30 balls). Serve immediately or store in the refrigerator until ready to serve (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["40 g freeze dried strawberries (2 packets - see Tips)","70 g puffed brown rice (see Tips)","180 g sunflower seeds","20 g coconut oil","240 g rice malt syrup","1 tbsp natural vanilla extract"]}],"id":"r119240","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-mTXa_OSf-_U\/XZWfGZfaMFI\/AAAAAAAAe-0\/NZKH7q5KFMAQ9pSlhfkWrR9Twuh7fbYUgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_njjFO7fYBvXUv9GM.png","title":"Strawberry amaze-balls","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0.6 g","fat":"0.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"2.7 g","calories":"89 kJ \/ 21 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, sealable container","hintsAndTricks":["You can use any flavour of freeze-dried fruit you wish (e.g. apple, pineapple, mango). You can buy freeze-dried fruit at most supermarkets in the tinned fruit aisle, at specialty food stores or online. We recommend using pure freeze-dried fruit (not combined with other ingredients).","You can buy puffed brown rice in the health food aisle at most major supermarkets.","You can serve these on a platter, as \"pops\" on wooden skewers or in mini-cupcake liners.","These will keep for 1 week in the refrigerator and up to 3 weeks in the freezer."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","30m","30 portions"]}